params._pyth: Address of the Pyth Network contract on this chain

params.decimals: Desired decimal places for the price

returns.priceInUsd: The price in USD with the specified decimals

returns.registered: True if price feed is registered

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.priceUpdateData: Encoded price update data from Pyth

constructor.notice: Initialize the PriceOracle with Pyth Network contract

getPrice(address).notice: Get the current price for a token

getPriceFeedId(address).notice: Get the price feed ID for a token

getPriceInUsd(address,uint8).notice: Get the USD price for a token with specified decimals

getPriceUnsafe(address).notice: Get the latest price without age check (use with caution)

getUpdateFee(bytes[]).notice: Get the update fee for updating price feeds

hasPriceFeed(address).notice: Check if a token has a registered price feed

maxPriceAge().notice: Maximum age of price data in seconds (default: 60 seconds)

priceFeedToToken(bytes32).notice: Mapping of Pyth price feed ID to token address

registerPriceFeed(address,bytes32).notice: Register a price feed for a token

tokenToPriceFeed(address).notice: Mapping of token address to Pyth price feed ID

updatePriceFeeds(bytes[]).notice: Update price feeds with new data from Pyth Network
